% The longest shortest path between any two nodes nodes in the network% INPUTS: adjacency matrix, adj% OUTPUTS: network diameter, diam% Gergana Bounova, Last updated: October 19, 2009%update by Jesse Blocher December 2009 because diamter is not taking max%distance, just the max of that last i.function diam = diameter(adj)n = numnodes(adj);diams = zeros(1,n);for i=1:numnodes(adj)    d=simple_dijkstra(adj,i);    diams(i) = max(d);enddiam = max(diams);